name: Shapley Value Sampling
text: This method involves taking a random permutation of the input features and adding them one-by-one to the given baseline.

name: Distribution of Shapley Value Sampling attribution values
Feature Permutation
text: It takes each input feature, permutes the feature values within a batch, and computes the difference between original and shuffled outputs for the given batch.

name: Feature Ablation
text: A perturbation based approach for computing attribution, involving replacing each input feature with a given baseline / reference, and computing the difference in output.

name: Guided Backpropagation
text: calculates the gradient of the output with respect to the input but varies in the backpropagation of ReLU functions, where gradients are backpropagated only when both the gradient and input are positive.

name: Input X Gradient
text: It multiplies input with the gradient with respect to input.

name: Distribution of Input X Gradient values
Gradient Shap
text: Gradient Shap approximates SHAP values by computing the expectations of gradients.

name: Deep Lift
text: DeepLIFT explains the difference in output from some ‘reference’ output in terms of the difference of the input from some ‘reference’ input

name: Saliency
text: Assigns Importance score to each feature by returning gradients wrt inputs.

name: Integrated Gradients
text: Assigns Importance score to each input feature by approximating the integral of gradients.

name: Distribution of Integrated Gradients attribution values
